{"questionId":"13916319","questionHtml":"<p>If the model is correct, describe the shape of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> against <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mi>c</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;gradient is a constant&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>so the graph should be a straight line&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13916319","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.1bi","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"If the model is correct, describe the shape of the graph of v against t.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.10—Second derivatives, testing for max and min"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}